@startuml Hajj and Umrah Travel Aggregator - Business Flow

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

title Hajj and Umrah Travel Aggregator - Business Data Flow

actor "Admin User" as Admin
actor "Customer" as Customer
participant "Back Office\n(React Admin)" as BackOffice
participant "Customer Portal\n(React.js)" as Portal
participant "API Gateway" as Gateway
participant "Scraping Service" as Scraper
participant "Package Service" as PackageService
participant "Recommendation\nService" as Recommender
participant "Training Service" as Trainer
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
database "Vector DB" as VectorDB

== Data Collection Phase ==

Admin -> BackOffice: Configure scraping targets
activate BackOffice
BackOffice -> Gateway: POST /admin/scraping/targets
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Scraper: Schedule scraping jobs
activate Scraper

Scraper -> Scraper: Scrape travel agency websites\n(concurrent virtual threads)
note right
  Scrape:
  - Package details
  - Prices & dates
  - Services included
  - Contact information
  - Departure cities
  - Testimonials
end note

Scraper -> PackageService: Store scraped data
activate PackageService
PackageService -> DB: Insert packages, agencies,\ntestimonials, contact info
PackageService -> VectorDB: Generate & store\npackage embeddings
deactivate PackageService
deactivate Scraper
deactivate Gateway
deactivate BackOffice

== Customer Interaction Phase ==

Customer -> Portal: Browse packages
activate Portal
Portal -> Gateway: GET /packages
activate Gateway
Gateway -> PackageService: Fetch packages
activate PackageService
PackageService -> DB: Query packages
DB --> PackageService: Package data
PackageService --> Gateway: Package list
deactivate PackageService
Gateway --> Portal: Package list
Portal --> Customer: Display packages
deactivate Gateway

Customer -> Portal: Enter preferences\n(budget, dates, services,\ndeparture city, etc.)
Portal -> Gateway: POST /preferences
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Recommender: Get recommendations\nbased on preferences
activate Recommender

Recommender -> VectorDB: Generate preference\nembedding & search similar
VectorDB --> Recommender: Similar packages
Recommender -> DB: Fetch full package details
DB --> Recommender: Package details with\ntestimonials
Recommender -> Recommender: Apply classification model\nto rank results
Recommender --> Gateway: Ranked recommendations
deactivate Recommender
Gateway --> Portal: Recommendations
deactivate Gateway
Portal --> Customer: Display personalized\nrecommendations
deactivate Portal

Customer -> Portal: View package details\n& testimonials
Portal -> Gateway: GET /packages/{id}
activate Gateway
Gateway -> PackageService: Get package details
activate PackageService
PackageService -> DB: Fetch package,\nagency, testimonials
DB --> PackageService: Complete data
PackageService --> Gateway: Package details
deactivate PackageService
Gateway --> Portal: Full package info
deactivate Gateway
Portal --> Customer: Display details with\ncontact & testimonials

Customer -> Portal: Save preference\n& interaction
Portal -> Gateway: POST /interactions
activate Gateway
Gateway -> PackageService: Log interaction
activate PackageService
PackageService -> DB: Store interaction data
deactivate PackageService
deactivate Gateway

== Training & Improvement Phase ==

Admin -> BackOffice: Initiate model training
activate BackOffice
BackOffice -> Gateway: POST /admin/training/start
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Trainer: Start training job
activate Trainer

Trainer -> DB: Fetch historical data\n(interactions, preferences,\nconversions)
DB --> Trainer: Training dataset
Trainer -> Trainer: Train classification model\n& fine-tune embeddings
note right
  Training includes:
  - Customer preference patterns
  - Successful conversions
  - Click-through data
  - Rating patterns
end note

Trainer -> DB: Update model metadata
Trainer -> VectorDB: Update embeddings
Trainer --> Gateway: Training complete
deactivate Trainer
Gateway --> BackOffice: Success status
deactivate Gateway
BackOffice --> Admin: Training completed
deactivate BackOffice

== Analytics & Monitoring ==

Admin -> BackOffice: View analytics
activate BackOffice
BackOffice -> Gateway: GET /admin/analytics
activate Gateway
Gateway -> PackageService: Get statistics
activate PackageService
PackageService -> DB: Query analytics data
DB --> PackageService: Stats & metrics
PackageService --> Gateway: Analytics data
deactivate PackageService
Gateway --> BackOffice: Dashboard data
deactivate Gateway
BackOffice --> Admin: Display analytics\n(popular packages,\nconversion rates, etc.)
deactivate BackOffice

@enduml
